title: Known Sub-Sequence Algorithm
text: package implements Known Sub-Sequence Algorithm <doi: 10.1016/j.aaf.2021.12.013> helps automatically compare, validate identify best methods missing data imputation time series. compares performance 11 state---art’s imputation methods avaliable multiple CRAN packages delivers best method suited particular time series.

title: Known Sub-Sequence Algorithm
text: can install development version kssa like :

title: Known Sub-Sequence Algorithm
text: can run kssa like following example plots results obtained applying kssa example time series tsAirgapComplete.  Conclusion: Since kssa_plot ordered lower higher error (left right), method ‘linear_i’ best impute missing data airgap_na_ts. Notice method ‘locf’ worst obtain imputations best method, method preference use function get_imputations().
code: # Create 20% random missing data in tsAirgapComplete time series from imputeTS set.seed(1234) library("kssa") library("imputeTS") airgap_na <- missMethods::delete_MCAR(as.data.frame(tsAirgapComplete), 0.2)  # Convert co2_na to time series object airgap_na_ts <- ts(airgap_na, start = c(1959, 1), end = c(1997, 12), frequency = 12)  # Apply the kssa algorithm with 5 segments, # 10 iterations, 20% of missing data, and # compare among all available methods in the package. # Remember that percentmd must match with # the real percentage of missing data in the # input co2_na_ts time series  results_kssa <- kssa(airgap_na_ts,   start_methods = "all",   actual_methods = "all",   segments = 5,   iterations = 10,   percentmd = 0.2 )  kssa_plot(results_kssa, type = "complete", metric = "rmse")

text: x_ts ts object missing data imputed methods string string vector indicating method methods can choose following: "" - get imputed values methods - Default "auto.arima" - State space representation ARIMA model "StructTS" - State space representation structural model "seadec" - Seasonal decomposition Kalman smoothing "linear_i" - Linear interpolation "spline_i" - Spline interpolation "stine_i" - Stineman interpolation "simple_ma" - Simple moving average "linear_ma" - Linear moving average "exponential_ma" - Exponential moving average "locf" - Last observation carried forward "stl" - Seasonal trend decomposition Loess details imputation methods please check packages imputeTS forecast seed Numeric. number

title: kssa Algorithm — kssa
text: x_ts Time series object ts containing missing data (NA) start_methods String vector. method methods start algorithm. actual_methods actual_methods imputation methods compared validated. can string vector containing following can choose following: "" - compare among methods automatically - Default "auto.arima" - State space representation ARIMA model "StructTS" - State space representation structural model "seadec" - Seasonal decomposition Kalman smoothing "linear_i" - Linear interpolation "spline_i" - Spline interpolation "stine_i" - Stineman interpolation "simple_ma" - Simple moving average "linear_ma" - Linear moving average "exponential_ma" - Exponential moving average "locf" - Last observation carried forward "stl" - Seasonal trend decomposition Loess details imputation methods please check packages imputeTS forecast segments Integer. many segments time series divided iterations Integer. many iterations run percentmd Numeric. Percentage missing data. Must match true percentage missing data x_ts seed Numeric. Random seed choose
